    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A music library app is getting ready to sort songs in a playlist alphabetically by title. As a first step, the app compares two song titles using <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">compareTo()</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Library</code> class, complete the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">compareSongs()</code> method. This method should:\r\n\r\n- Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">compareTo()</code> to compare two song titles\r\n- Return the result of that comparison as an integer\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">LibraryRunner</code> class, create a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Library</code> object using two songs, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">compareSongs()</code> method, and print the result.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">compareTo()</code> returns:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>a negative number if the first title comes before the second</li>\r\n  <li>zero if the titles are equal</li>\r\n  <li>a positive number if the first title comes after the second</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n",
